name: Maguuma's Mantle Skin
description:
This will replace the appearance of one shoulder armor of any weight class and unlock the skin in your account wardrobe.

This shoulder skin has no stats of its own.

name: Ragamuffin Cape
description: An enhanced version of the standard Ragamuffin armor.

name: Duty-Bound Brigandine
description: An enhanced version of the standard Duty-Bound armor.

details.name: Explorer Boost
details.description:
Increase movement speed by 15%.
Gain 10 seconds of swiftness when gathering.
33% chance at extra resources when gathering.
Increase experience gained from kills by 50%
<c=@reminder>Will be removed if you enter competitive PvP or a raid.</c>

name: Ragamuffin Grips
description: An enhanced version of the standard Ragamuffin armor.

name: Equip a pair of enhanced boots.

name: Enhanced Mighty Leggings
description: Double-click to open. Contains leggings that are more powerful than standard level 5 leggings.

name: Beginner Map Portal Note
description: Double-click to choose which zone you want to teleport to. Teleporting consumes 1 of 5 charges. <c=@Warning>This item cannot be used while in combat.</c>

description: Unlocks the reward track for the Guildrider Warclaw skin.

name: Collector's Box
description: Double-click to open. Contains a choice of a level 10 Enhanced Mighty weapon, 3 choices of dye unlocks, 5 transmutation charges, and a Royal Terrace two-week pass.

name: Mighty Blind Ed's Longbow
description: An enhanced version of the standard Mighty weapon.

name: Duty-Bound Domeplate
description: An enhanced version of the standard Duty-Bound armor.

name: Glyph of Overload
description: Double-click to apply this to a gathering tool.

buff.description: Applies the Overload special action skill when fully charged, which grants +100% chance of extra gathering strikes while charges are available. Gather from resource nodes to build charges. Harvesting nodes consume additional charges.

name: Encounter Report
description: <c=@flavor>"We heard fighting over the ridge, but Ryland ordered us to hold the pass. If we chased the fight, we would have been surrounded."</c>

name: Steel Warband Combat Blade of Accuracy
Black Citadel Gate Link
description: Adds the Black Citadel as a destination to the Eye of the North gate.

name: Chest of the Visionary Echoes

name: Unlock Merchant
description: Adds a basic vendor to the Eye of the North.

name: Koss on Koss: Unauthorized and Uncensored
description:
<c=@flavor>A Sunspear never fights alone.</c>
Found in the Eye of the North.

name: Brand Crystal
description: Grants credit toward collecting a Branded Trophy.

name: Dark Wing Staff Skin
description: Double-click to apply this look to any other staff.

name: Metal Legion Ticket Stub
description: <c=@flavor>"Metal Legion crowds are the pits."</c>

name: Dark Wing Dagger Skin
description: Double-click to apply this look to any other dagger.

name: Unlock Cooking Station
description: Adds a cooking station to the Eye of the North.

name: Transcendence
description: <c=@flavor>Rise above it all.</c>

name: Recipe: Iron Legion Staff
description: A recipe to make an Iron Legion Staff.

name: Reconsideration
description: <c=@flavor>"Got chased in here by the biggest Branded devourer I'd ever seen. Thought I'd starve to death. Never thought I'd see a human lure it away."</c>

name: Redeployment Order
description: <c=@flavor>"Vishen Steelshot: immediately regroup with Steel warband at Terra Carorunda Waypoint for an important assignment."</c>

name: Disappointment
description: <c=@flavor>"I went renegade because they said we'd be heroes when we eradicated the humans for good, but here I am sitting in a dank cave sharpening rusty swords."</c>

name: Secret of the Raven Reflector
description: <c=@flavor>"Scouted a reflector overlooking a Bear shrine. Lines up with others nearby. Then spotted the tower to the southwest..."

name: Dark Wing Shield Skin
description: Double-click to apply this look to any other shield.

name: Dark Wing Scepter Skin
description: Double-click to apply this look to any other scepter.

name: Echo of Whispers
description: Double-click to open. Contains loot found in medium essence chests or rewarded from earning silver rank in the Whisper of Jormag Strike Mission.

name: The Ebonlocke Covenant
description:
<c=@flavor>Love is a battlefield.</c>
Confiscated from the Brig in Grothmar Valley.

name: The Passions of Faren
description:
<c=@flavor>He's rich...with a burning passion!</c>
Banned for sedition against the God King and sealed in the warehouse of Vehtendi Academy in the Domain of Vabbi.

name: Journal Scrap
description: <c=@flavor>"First Posting: On loan to Reave warband in Redreave Mill. Mountain makes sentry duty easy. Good sight lines. Campfire talk says there's a killer festival at Butcher's Block."</c>

name: Emblem of Tournament Victory
description: In the Mystic Forge, combine Slumbering Transcendence, 250 Unidentified Dyes, an Emblem of Tournament Victory, and an Essence of Llamatic Elegance to create Transcendence.

name: Hoelbrak Gate Link
description: Adds Hoelbrak as a destination to the Eye of the North gate.

name: Salt-Forged Mist Diamond
description: In the Mystic Forge, combine a Salt-Forged Mist Diamond with a Gift of the Mists, a Gift of Competitive Dedication, and 100 Icy Runestones to create Gift of the Champion.

name: Love Is Blind
description:
<c=@flavor>Hearts collide in the frigid tunnels of the Shiverpeaks.</c>
Found in the Grotto in Thunderhead Peaks.

name: Distilled Hylek Mead
description:
<c=@flavor>"Burns long, hot, and clean. Perfect for a flaming sword."
—Vash</c>

name: Charred Slip of Paper
description: <c=@flavor>"Tribune, the renegade that just pledged Blood in the trials would be a fine addition to Steel. Make it happen, but do not show my hand.  —B"</c>

name: Emblem of Victory
description: In the Mystic Forge, combine a Vial of Salt, an Emblem of Victory, a Mist Diamond, and a Mist-Enhanced Orichalcum to create a Salt-Forged Mist Diamond.

name: Pristine Fang of the Whisper
description:
Can be attained from the Whisper of Jormag.
Trade to Berghild in Eye of the North for boots.

name: Shattered Chest Lid
description: <c=@flavor>"This chest has been puzzling me for a while. I see no way to reach the mechanism through this field...unless you're a tank-mounted harpoon."</c>

name: Broken Rod
description:
<c=@flavor>"Our primus used to beat us with a rod to toughen us up, until one day he didn't."
—Ryland Steelcatcher</c>

name: Ash Legion Combat Blade of Celerity
Resistance
description: <c=@flavor>"Some of the warband are starting to eye each other in the wrong way. Got to silence the whispers."</c>

—Crystallographer Smoxxi</c>
